South Africa’s main stock benchmark erases gains of as much as 0.4% to drop for a fourth day Friday, down 0.4% by 10:06 a.m. in Johannesburg. The four-day slide, the benchmark’s longest losing streak since June 11, deepens weekly losses to 2.1%. An index of South African banking stocks drops 1.6%, surrendering an advance of as much as 0.9%, after Investec said it sees first-half profit falling as much as 68% in the wake of the coronavirus pandemic.